news.title: US regulator sues Berkshire owned lender for making risky home loans
news.para: Vanderbilt Mortgage and Finance, a unit of Clayton, allegedly ignored "clear and obvious red flags" that borrowers could not afford their loans, and failed to properly assess borrowers' ability to pay other debts and keep food on the table.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: MPIDC acquires 400 hectare of land to develop Vikram Udyogpuri phase II
news.para: At present, Vikram Udyogpuri spans 458 hectare and is nearly at full capacity. The process of taking possession of the new land has already began, and a detailed project report will be prepared to initiate the development.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Construction work of Trichy Tidel park to begin this month
news.para: City corporation sources said 14.1 acre of land on Trichy-Madurai NH, adjacent to the upcoming integrated bus terminus (IBT), has been allocated to Tidel management for building the park in two phases.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 825 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: ​​The civic body sealed properties of defaulters in complexes such as Rakhial Arhat Industrial Estate, Akshat Estate, Sumel Business Park, Khokhra Radhe Mall, and Nikol Akshar Arcade.

news.title: E-khata system leads to drop in Karnataka property registrations in December 2024
news.para: According to the stamps and registration department, the slowdown in registrations has caused a shortfall of Rs 1,971 crore in revenue from stamp duty and registration fees, compared to the target of Rs 18,388 crore for Dec 2024.

news.title: Mumbai: SIT finds 63 more forged land records, 165 so far
news.para: The tampering, which facilitated unauthorised construction on hundreds of properties along Mumbai suburban coastline, involves a nexus of govt officials, contractors, and estate agents, according to SIT.

news.title: Allahabad HC slams LDA, civic body over delay in demolishing illegal constructions in Lucknow
news.para: The Lucknow bench of the court termed the situation as "unpleasant" and said it may have worsened by time.

news.title: Noida authority reclaims floodplain land worth Rs 480 crore from encroachers
news.para: The land, located in Sorkha village and valued at around Rs 480 crore, was occupied by colonisers who had constructed boundary walls and plotted the area for unauthorised sale.

news.title: US sues Cushman & Wakefield, other landlords over alleged rental price coordination
news.para: The DOJ and a coalition of states sued in North Carolina in August, accusing property management software company RealPage of letting landlords collude by sharing their pricing information with the company's software, which then recommends rent prices.

news.title: SC sets aside Bombay HC order to transfer five-acre Worli land to Century Textiles
news.para: The SC order paved the way for BMC to take possession of the land which was given from 1927 for 28 years at a yearly rent of Re 1 though no step was taken to take it back after the lease expired.

news.title: Sobha records sales value of Rs 13.88 billion in Q3 FY25
news.para: Average realization improved by 31.3% over same period last year to Rs 14,226 per sq ft, aided by price increases in ongoing projects and higher realization in the new project launches during the year.

news.title: ASK Property Fund, India Sotheby's launch Rs 1,000 crore real estate fund
news.para: ASK Property Fund is the real estate private equity arm of Blackstone-backed ASK Asset & Wealth Management Group.

news.title: Noida authority directs Suraksha Realty to maintain Jaypee Kosmos till CCs issued
news.para: The Authority, during a mediation meeting on Jan 6, warned of legal action if Suraksha did not provide the services till completion certificate was granted to the partially completed project.

news.title: Varun Dhawan buys apartment for Rs 44.5 crore in Mumbai’s Juhu
news.para: The couple has acquired the property spread over 5,512 sq ft on the seventh floor of an under-construction tower, Twenty, from home furnishings company D'décor Exports Pvt Ltd.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP identifies 50% houses in DLF areas violating norms
news.para: The violations include illegal constructions and carrying out commercial activities, such as having paying guest accommodations and guest houses, running from residential buildings.

news.title: Puravankara appoints Deepak Rastogi as Group CFO
news.para: Neeraj Gautam, who has been serving as the president-finance at Puravankara, has been elevated to the post of deputy chief financial officer.

news.title: UK construction growth slows to six-month low: Survey
news.para: The S&P Global Purchasing Managers' Index for the construction sector dropped to 53.3 in December from November's 55.2, its lowest since June and below all forecasts in a Reuters poll of economists.

news.title: Signature Global reports pre-sales of Rs 27.7 billion in Q3 FY25
news.para: With this, Signature Global has achieved 87% of its sales guidance of Rs 100 billion for FY25. Average pre-sales realisation for 9M FY25 grew to Rs 12,565 per sq ft compared to Rs 11,762 per sq ft in FY24.

news.title: House prices in UK drop by 0.2% in December 2024: Halifax
news.para: Halifax, part of Lloyds Banking Group, Britain's biggest mortgage lender, said house prices fell 0.2% in December after a 1.2% rise in November, and were 3.3% higher on the year - lower than the 4.2% rise forecast in a Reuters poll of economists.

news.title: Trichy: Police booked five people for illegal sand mining
news.para: The Srirangam police confiscated one unit of sand from a mini truck at a vacant plot in Tagore Street service road on Trichy – Chennai national highway near Srirangam.
